Step 1: Create a Model for Today’s Specials
# models.py
from django.db import models

class TodaySpecial(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=100)
    description = models.TextField()
    price = models.DecimalField(max_digits=6, decimal_places=2)
    is_active = models.BooleanField(default=True)  # to mark current specials

    def __str__(self):
        return self.name


 Step 2: Run Migrations
 python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate


 Step 3: Add Some Specials via Admin or Shell
 Register the model in admin.py:
 from django.contrib import admin
from .models import TodaySpecial

admin.site.register(TodaySpecial)

 add from the shell:
 python manage.py shell
from your_app.models import TodaySpecial
TodaySpecial.objects.create(name="Paneer Tikka", description="Grilled paneer cubes with spices", price=249.00)
TodaySpecial.objects.create(name="Butter Naan", description="Soft Indian bread topped with butter", price=49.00)


Step 4: Update the Homepage View
from django.shortcuts import render
from .models import TodaySpecial
from datetime import datetime

def home_view(request):
    specials = TodaySpecial.objects.filter(is_active=True)
    context = {
        'specials': specials,
        'year': datetime.now().year,
    }
    return render(request, 'home.html', context)


Step 5: Update home.html Template
{% if specials %}
<div style="padding: 40px 20px; background-color: #f8f9fa;">
    <h2 style="text-align: center; font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 20px;">Today's Specials</h2>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: auto;">
        {% for item in specials %}
            <div style="background: white; padding: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 5px;">{{ item.name }}</h3>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 5px;">{{ item.description }}</p>
                <p style="font-weight: bold;">₹{{ item.price }}</p>
            </div>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</div>
{% endif %}


Result:
Now your homepage shows:
A "Today’s Specials" section
Data pulled from the database
Easy to update via admin panel or backend